duck: Elongation (astronomy) - In astronomy, a planet's elongation is the angle between the Sun and the planet, as viewed from Earth.
elongation definition: the angular distance of a celestial body from another around which it revolves or from a particular point in the sky.
Elongation (materials science) - Deformation in continuum mechanics is the transformation of a body from a reference configuration to a current configuration.

wiki.text:
'Elongation' may refer to: *Elongation (astronomy) *Elongation (materials
science) Or to biological processes: *Part of transcription of DNA into mRNA
*Part of eukaryotic or prokaryotic translation of mRNA
